- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper deals with network observations and vulnerabilities in cloud computing environments. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed framework uses machine learning techniques for anomaly detection. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper deals with handling big data generated in cloud computing environments and proposes a framework for efficient anomaly detection. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper provides technical functions and deployment details of the proposed framework, which can be considered as software engineering aspects.
